By Osagie Otabor, Akure  Ondo Governor, Oluwarotimi Akeredolu, has imposed a 7pm to 7am curfew on the state to curb further spread of COVID-19. He threatened to declare a total lockdown of the state if another COVID-19 case is discovered. Akeredolu clarified that the third case was not a member of the National Youth Service Corps but an employee of the Nigeria Army Clinic that served there in 2017. He ordered arrest and detention of any person caught during the curfew hours. The Ondo Governor said it was disturbing that a third COVID-19 case could be detected in the state despite measures put in place to curtail the spread. Akeredolu noted the stiffer measures being put in place was to stop COVID-19 from spreading across the state. Details shortlyâ€¦